Just curious, is there any particular reason why you are using SimpleITK rather than using itk?

The SimpleITK package has been around for much longer than itk. I have tried itk a couple of times, but I find it (even) less Pythonic and have never been able to make my tests run quickly. There was always some errors, bugs, features not implemented yet or just me being silly. TLDR: I have more experience with SimpleITK and they provide pretty much the same functionalities. PS: <denchmark-link:https://discourse.itk.org/t/should-i-switch-from-simpleitk-to-python-itk/1206>Should I switch from SimpleITK to Python ITK?</denchmark-link> .

ITK Python wrappers have improved tremendously over the past 1-2 years, so they are probably becoming better and more Pythonic than SimpleITK. ITK Python wrappers also allow all ITK-based libraries distributed as Python packages. So, I would expect that in the long term ITK Python wrappers will be used more widely. I still use SimpleITK for all processing, as it is more conveniently available in Slicer.
I would like to start using itk for next projects. I considered it for this project but decided it wasn't mature enough.
